Paper: hep-th/9404184

Date: 1994-04-29

Title: Mirror Symmetry as a Gauge Symmetry

Authors: Amit Giveon and Edward Witten

Comments: 11 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B332 (1994) 44-50

It is shown that in string theory mirror duality is a gauge symmetry (a Weyltransformation) in the moduli space of $N=2$ backgrounds on group manifolds,and we conjecture on the possible generalization to other backgrounds, such asCalabi-Yau manifolds.